  "notes": [
    "All transfer applicants must meet the University of California admissions eligibility requirements and the campus’s admission selection criteria. All requirements must be completed by the end of the spring term prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility and admission to UC Santa Cruz, visit the Admissions website . The UC Santa Cruz Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG) is a formal agreement that guarantees your fall admission to your chosen major, provided you are transferring from a California Community College and meet specific requirements. Visit the UC Santa Cruz TAG webpage for more information.",
    "THIS IS A SCREENING MAJOR. Screening majors require completion of specific preparatory coursework and/or a minimum GPA. For details on the specific screening requirements for this major, refer to the \" Transfer Admission Screening Policy \" below. Additional coursework listed under \"Recommended Preparation\" is not required for admission but is strongly recommended to support timely degree completion. For more information, including a list of screening majors and non-screening majors , visit the UCSC Admissions website.",
    "Some Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate Higher Level (IBH), and Advanced Level (A-level) exams satisfy UCSC course requirements. UCSC's exam credit policies may be found on the Degree Progress Unit website .",
    "Mathematics Education B.A. Transfer Admissions Screening Policy Transfer students must complete the following courses, or their articulated equivalents, with a grade of C (2.0) or better in each course by the end of the spring term prior to transferring in the fall: MATH 19A – Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics MATH 19B – Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics MATH 21 – Linear Algebra MATH 23A – Vector Calculus Refer to the \"Required Major Preparation Courses\" section below for lists of courses approved to fulfill these requirements. Strongly Recommended Major Preparation In addition to the required courses listed above, transfer students are strongly advised to complete STAT 5 – Statistics prior to transfer to ensure timely graduation. Additional Information for Transfer ﻿In obtaining equivalency for MATH 23A, transfer students may have completed a course that is also equivalent to MATH 23B. Students who have equivalency for MATH 23A but not MATH 23B are encouraged to contact the Mathematics department undergraduate adviser to determine if this applies to their situation. Students are strongly encouraged to prioritize required and recommended major preparation courses and may additionally complete courses that fulfill UC Santa Cruz general education requirements before transferring as time allows. Please visit the Mathematics website to learn more about this major. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Mathematics Education B.A. Program Statement"
